snippet: The American rider Andrew Talansky was the surprise winner of the Critérium du Dauphiné in Courchevel, France, as he held off the two-time Tour de France winner Alberto Contador in a gripping finale on the eighth stage.
abstract: American rider Andrew Talansky is surprise winner of Criterium du Dauphine bicycle race in Courchevel, France, as he holds off two-time Tour de France winner Alberto Contador in a gripping finale on the eighth stage.
lead_paragraph: The American rider Andrew Talansky was the surprise winner of the Critérium du Dauphiné in Courchevel, France, as he held off the two-time Tour de France winner Alberto Contador in a gripping finale on the eighth stage.
